<p>Let's say I type in the following code and format it.</p>  <pre><code>if (condition) { /* Hello! */ } </code></pre>  <p>If this is C# code, it is formatted like this:</p>  <pre><code>if (condition) {     // Hello! } </code></pre>  <p>If it is JavaScript, VSCode formats it like this:</p>  <pre><code>if (condition) {     // Hello! } </code></pre>  <p>So how can I use the first formatting style (curly braces on new lines) for all languages? I can't find a setting or something similar. Suggestions?</p>